data.enText: a person who knows a lot about a group or an organization, because they are part of it

data.chText: 据一名内部人士说，实情是乱作一团。
data.enText: The situation was described by one insider as ‘absolute chaos’.

simple_means.memory_skill: inside 内部 + er 人 → 局内人；知情人

tr: an officer of a corporation or others who have access to private information about the corporation's operations

value.def: An insider is someone who is involved in a situation and who knows more about it than other people.

example.ex: An insider said, 'Katharine has told friends it is time to end her career.'
example.tran: 一位知情人说：“凯瑟琳已告诉朋友准备结束她的事业”。

example.ex: German banks have more insider knowledge than most.
example.tran: 德国银行与大多数银行相比知晓更多的内部消息。

value.tran: 知情人;了解内幕者;消息灵通人士

trans: 内线交易，内幕交易(根据内线消息买卖股票的违法行为)
